Description: This corpus is available for download from the LINDAT repository.

Annotation: tokenisation, sentence segmentation, morphosyntactic tagging, lemmatisation and Named Entity recognition. Half of the corpus also syntactically parsed
Description: This corpus is available through the concordancers KonText and noSketchEngine and for download from the CLARIN.SI repository.

Annotation: syntactic parsing, labelling of semantic entities
Description: This corpus contains legal texts.#SEPThe corpus is available through the concordance KonText, the PML-TQ tool and for download from the LINDAT repository.
This corpus contains fictional texts.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from LINDAT and through the concordancer KonText.

This corpus is manually annotated at several levels – aside from syntactic parsing and morphological information, it is annotation for sentence information structure, multiword expression, coreference, bridging relations and discourse relations.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the LINDAT repository.

Annotation: syntactic parsing, mark-up of discourse phenomena enriched by the annotation of secondary connectives
Description: This corpus is a subset of the Prague Dependency Treebank 3.5#SEPThe corpus is available through the PML-TQ tool.
This syntactic parsing is modelled after the Prague Dependency Treebank.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the LINDAT repository.

This corpus is an extended version of Prague Czech-English Dependency Treebank 2.0, with added mark-up of coreference. The syntactic parsing follows the PDT 2.0 style.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the LINDAT repository. The version without coreference annotation is available through the concordancer KonText and the PML-TQ tool (Czech part only).

Annotation: syntactic parsing, mark-up of elliptical constructions
Description: This syntactic parsing follows the Universal Dependencies schema.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the LINDAT repository.
This corpus is available for download from the Dutch Language Institute and through the online environments PaQu and GrETEL.

Annotation: PoS tagging, syntactic parsing, semantic role labelling
Description: This is a manually annotated subset of the much larger (approx. 500 million) word) SoNaR corpus.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the Dutch Language Institute.
The corpus contains fictional and newspaper texts.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from META-SHARE (CELR distribution).

This corpus contains fictional, newspaper and scientific texts. The syntactic parsing follows the Universal Dependencies schema.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from META-SHARE (CELR distribution).

Corpus: TimeML annotated corpus of Estonian newspaper articles
Description: This corpus contains newspaper articles.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from META-SHARE (CELR distribution).
This corpus contains 19,000 sentences from the Large Grammar of Finnish.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the Language Bank of Finland.
This corpus contains 19,000 sentences from the Large Grammar of Finnish.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the Language Bank of Finland.
The syntactic parsing follows the Universal Dependencies schema.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the Turku BioNLP Group.

Corpus: Syntactic Reference Corpus of Medieval French
Description: This corpus contains Old French texts.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the IMS CLARIN-D repository.
The corpus is syntactically parsed following the TIGER guidelines.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from a dedicated website provided by the CLARIN-D consortium.
This corpus contains historical German texts.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the HZSK repository.

Corpus: Dependency-Annotated Subset of the CREG Corpus
Description: This corpus consists of answers to reading comprehension questions written by American college students learning German.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the Tübingen CLARIN Repository.

Corpus: Tübingen Treebank of Written German / Newspaper Corpus (TüBa-D/Z)
Description: This corpus contains newspaper articles.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the Tübingen CLARIN Repository.
This corpus is available for download from a dedicated webpage.

This corpus contains Icelandic texts from the 12th through the 21st centuries – approximately 100,000 words from each century. The corpus is syntactically parsed following the UUPenn scheme for historical textse#SEPThe corpus is available for online search through treebankstudio.org and for download in different formats from a dedicated webpage.
This treebank is manually annotated according to a hybrid dependency-constituency grammar.#SEPThe treebank is available for download from the CLARIN-LV repository.
Syntactic parsing follows the rules of the Prague Dependency Treebank#SEPThis corpus is available for download from the CLARIN-LT repository. The second version is available upon request.

Corpus: Polish Dependency Bank in Universal Dependency format
Description: This corpus also contains sentences showing certain problematic syntactic phenomena – sentences with ellipsis, comparative constructions, constructions with the bi-functional subordinating conjunction jako, etc. The syntactic parsing follows the Universal Dependencies schema.#SEPThe first version of the corpus is available for download from the Computational Linguistics in Poland website. The second version is available upon request.
This corpus contains literary and newspaper texts.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the PORTULAN CLARIN repository.
This corpus contains literary and newspaper texts.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the PORTULAN CLARIN repository.

Annotation: PoS-tagging, syntactic parsing, grammatical functions, logical forms
Description: This corpus contains literary and newspaper texts.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the PORTULAN CLARIN repository.

Annotation: syntactic parsing and phrase semantic roles
Description: This corpus contains literary and newspaper texts.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the ELRA catalogue.

Annotation: tokenisation, sentence segmentation, morphosyntactic tagging, lemmatisation, syntactic parsing, and Named Entity recognition
Description: This corpus contains posts from the Southeast European Times news portal, which is now defunct. The syntactic parsing follows the Universal Dependencies framework.#SEPThe corpus is available through the concordancers KonText and noSketchEngine and for download from the CLARIN.SI repository.
The syntactic parsing follows the rules of the https://ufal.mff.cuni.cz/pdt/.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the LINDAT repository.
